  <!-- GETTING STARTED -->
  <section class="how" id="how">
    <div class="how-inner">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <div class="tag">Getting Started</div>
        <h2>Three ways to work with diagrams.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="how-grid reveal-stagger">
        <div class="how-col">
          <h3 class="how-subtitle">Auto-render from your doc</h3>
          <p class="how-subtitle-desc">Already have Mermaid code? Render everything in one click.</p>
          <div class="timeline">
            <div class="tl-item"><h4>Write Mermaid syntax</h4><p>Place your diagram code inside a code block in your Google Doc.</p></div>
            <div class="tl-item"><h4>Run the renderer</h4><p><strong>Extensions → Mermaid Toolkit → Convert All Code to Diagrams.</strong> Every diagram gets rendered.</p></div>
            <div class="tl-item"><h4>Insert into your document</h4><p>Preview each diagram, then click <strong>Insert</strong> or <strong>Replace</strong>. Done.</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="how-col">
          <h3 class="how-subtitle">Use the built-in editor</h3>
          <p class="how-subtitle-desc">Write diagrams from scratch with live preview and templates.</p>
          <div class="timeline">
            <div class="tl-item"><h4>Open the editor</h4><p><strong>Extensions → Mermaid Toolkit → Insert Mermaid Diagram.</strong></p></div>
            <div class="tl-item"><h4>Write and preview</h4><p>Write or paste Mermaid syntax on the left, see the <strong>live preview</strong> update on the right.</p></div>
            <div class="tl-item"><h4>Insert into your document</h4><p>Pick a <strong>template</strong> to get started quickly, then click <strong>Insert at Cursor</strong>.</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="how-col how-col-full">
          <h3 class="how-subtitle">Fix pasted markdown</h3>
          <p class="how-subtitle-desc">Copied Mermaid code from a markdown file or another tool? Google Docs corrupts it. Fix it in one step.</p>
          <div class="timeline">
            <div class="tl-item"><h4>Open Fix Copied Markdown</h4><p><strong>Extensions → Mermaid Toolkit → Fix Copied Markdown.</strong></p></div>
            <div class="tl-item"><h4>Paste your broken code</h4><p>Paste the corrupted markdown. The tool shows a side-by-side diff of what it will fix.</p></div>
            <div class="tl-item"><h4>Copy the fixed result</h4><p>Click <strong>Copy Fixed</strong> and paste it back into your doc — ready to render.</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="callout reveal">
        <strong>Heads up:</strong> The first line of your code block must be a diagram type keyword.
        <div class="callout-compare">
          <div class="callout-do">
            <span class="callout-label do">Do</span>
            <div class="code-block"><div class="code-line">graph TD</div><div class="code-line hl-ok">  %% comments after line 1 are ok!</div><div class="code-line">  A --&gt; B</div><div class="code-line">  B --&gt; C</div><div class="code-line">  C --&gt; D</div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="callout-dont">
            <span class="callout-label dont">Don't</span>
            <div class="code-block"><div class="code-line hl-bad">%% this breaks detection!</div><div class="code-line">graph TD</div><div class="code-line">  A --&gt; B</div><div class="code-line">  B --&gt; C</div><div class="code-line">  C --&gt; D</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

